wiki.content: "To. X" is the lead single from South Korean singer Taeyeon's fifth Korean-language extended play (EP) of the same name, released on November 27, 2023, by SM Entertainment. The song is an R&B track that combines sensuous guitar riffs and rhythmic melodies, with lyrics written by Kenzie. The composition and arrangement were handled by Stephen Puth, Dazy, and Kristin Carpenter. Thematically, "To. X" addresses the end of a controlling relationship, with Taeyeon singing about realizing the other person's manipulative behavior. The song is composed in A-flat minor with a tempo of 97 beats per minute, creating a melancholic yet empowering atmosphere. The music video for "To. X" visually complements the song's narrative, depicting Taeyeon reflecting on a toxic relationship and ultimately burning down the home they built together, symbolizing her liberation. The EP "To. X" includes six tracks, each exploring different facets of relationships and personal growth. The tracklist is as follows: 1. "To. X" – 2:50 2. "Melt Away" – 3:16 3. "Burn It Down" – 2:50 4. "Nightmare" (악몽) – 2:55 5. "All For Nothing" – 3:10 6. "Fabulous" – 2:51 The EP was promoted through various live events, including a "Countdown Live" on YouTube, TikTok, Weverse, and Idol Plus. Taeyeon also performed "To. X" live at the SM Town Live 2024: SMCU Palace in Tokyo. "To. X" received positive reviews for its emotional depth and Taeyeon's vocal performance. It debuted at number three on South Korea's Circle Digital Chart and won several awards, including multiple wins on music shows like Inkigayo and Show! Music Core. Read more on Last.fm.
